extendedInfo.description: Enjoy the convenience, security and ease of doing your banking right from your mobile device. You can check your account balances, transfer funds, view recent activity, receive alerts, find ATMs or banking centers - even make check deposits from your phone.To get started, download and launch the app. Then sign on with your Academy Bank Midwest Online Banking Access ID and Password. Itâs that simple.Monitor Your Account - See account balances and transaction historyPerform Transactions- Pay bills- Transfer money between Academy Bank Midwest accounts- Place a stop paymentMake Check Deposits- Make check deposits with your phone Find Branch Locations and ATMs- Find the nearest Academy Bank Midwest banking center locations & ATMs- Speak with a bank representativeAlerts- Balance level alerts:  let you know when you have gone above or dipped below your pre-selected amount. - Transaction alerts:  let you know when specific transaction activity occurs on your account. - Scheduled alerts:  send you the latest information on your available balance and recent account history.Safe and SecureAcademy Bank Midwest is committed to your security and protecting the privacy of your financial information. We use state of the art technology to protect unauthorized access to your account, your wireless communication is securely encrypted, and your personal information is not stored on your phone. Have Questions?  Call 1-866-868-9141 Academy Bank a Division of Armed Forces Bank â Member FDIC

reviews.title: Very exciting
reviews.comment: I\'m so glad Academy has made this app for us. I\'ve seen other banking apps and am very impressed by this one. It\'s very easy to use and from what I\'ve seen keeps up to date with your account almost instantly. Thanks Academy.
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Thank you!
reviews.comment: Nice to be able to deposit checks now without driving 35 miles to nearest bank. For those having problems with sending images, wait about 30 secs or so after sending front image before taking back picture, only way it worked for me.
